        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 2:44AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 244 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Milton, or 10 miles southeast of Bloomfield, moving northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Milton around 250 AM CDT.
Keosauqua around 300 AM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Stockport,
Hillsboro and Westwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
